    h1#page-title Sushi

  p#instructions You just arrived for the first time at a sushi restaurant and the menu has no pictures! Learn the different types of sushi and fish, how to eat them and what they pair with.


  section#sushi-types
    h2 Types of Sushi

    .items
      article.item
        img(src='assets/img/food/nigiri.jpeg')
        p.caption Nigiri
        p.description a slice of raw fish atop a small mound of rice and with a little #[i wasabi] between them.
        p.extra-info Eaten with hands, fish side down on tongue first.
        p.extra-info Flip on its side, gently dip fish edge in soy sauce (not rice), don't shake it. Not with wasabi.

      article.item
        img(src='assets/img/food/maki.jpeg')
        p.caption Maki
        p.description strips of fish laid in rice and rolled inside #[i nori] in a long cylinder, then cut in small pieces
        p.extra-info Futomaki: thick rolls, Hosomaki: thin rolls
        p.extra-info Traditionally eaten with hands: thumb and middle finger.

      article.item
        img(src='assets/img/food/uramaki.jpeg')
        p.caption Uramaki
        p.description inside-out roll: fish in the center wrapped in #[i nori] and rice on the outside

      article.item
        img(src='assets/img/food/sashimi.jpeg')
        p.caption Sashimi
        p.description raw slices of fish (not considered sushi).
        p.extra-info Eaten with chopsticks. Can mix soy sauce & wasabi



