  section#more-info
    h2 More Info

    h3 Eating
    ul
      li Eat immediately, before it loses flavor
      li Eat #[i maki] first, before it loses crispiness
      li Eat should eaten in one bite, to avoid ruining the structure
      li Eat most flavorful last: white fish, silver, red, salmon, fattest; to avoid overpowering lighter fish

    h3 Chopsticks
    ul
      li Use back ends when taking from another plate
      li Don't pass food with them, extend your plate instead
      li Don't point with them
      li Don't rub them together
      li Don't stick them vertically in rice
      li When resting, place them on the ceramic rest

    h3 Chef
    ul
      li #[i Omakase] = meal of dishes selected by the chef
      li You can sit at the bar to watch preparation (non-sushi items ordered from waiter)
      li You can ask about tools; but asking about freshness of ingredients is insulting
      li You can complement with #[i Sake] or beer but you can't tip

    h3 Etiquette
    ul
      li Don't leave food on the plate, at all
      li Be aware when taking photos
      li Towels may be provided to wipe hands before eating

    h3 Related Terms
    ul
      li #[i itamae] = sushi chef
      li #[i irasshaimase] = welcome
      li #[i toro] = fat
      li #[i sushi] initially referred to the rice

